        <title>Linux: Extract audio and video using ffmpeg </title>
        <link>https://manios.org/2014/07/28/linux-extract-audio-and-video-using-ffmpeg/</link>
        <pubDate>Mon, 28 Jul 2014 14:21:08 +0300</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://manios.org/2014/07/28/linux-extract-audio-and-video-using-ffmpeg/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Today I had some mp4 video files and I wanted to extract the audio and video into separate files. So to do that you can do the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;extract-audio-from-video-file-and-convert-it-to-mp3&#34;&gt;Extract audio from video file and convert it to mp3
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To accomplish that, execute the command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ffmpeg -i logothetis-bureaucracy.mp4  -ab 128k -ac &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; -ar &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;44100&lt;/span&gt; -vn logothetis-bureaucracy.mp3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;extract-only-the-video-segment-from-a-video&#34;&gt;Extract only the video segment from a video
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To accomplish that, execute the command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ffmpeg -i video.wmv -vcodec copy -an onlyvideo.wmv 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description>
